                        <span class="text-primary-600">06.</span> How to Verify 16 KB Page Alignment
                    </h2>
                    <p class="text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-4">
                        After building the APK, you can run automated checks locally to confirm that all compiled libraries in the APK adhere strictly to 16 KB boundary requirements.
                    </p>

                    <div class="space-y-4">
                        <div class="p-4 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl border border-slate-100">
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 text-sm mb-2">Method 1: APK Analyzer (Recommended)</h4>
                            <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-1">
                                <li>Drag and drop the generated <code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 text-slate-700 font-mono">.apk</code> into Android Studio.</li>
                                <li>Navigate into the <code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 text-slate-700 font-mono">lib/</code> folder.</li>
                                <li>Inspect individual libraries in the table. Verify that the 16 KB support column indicates success/compliance. Since <code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 text-slate-700 font-mono">libmlkit_google_ocr_pipeline.so</code> is now completely removed from our built package, there is zero 4 KB residue remaining in ML Kit!</li>
                            </ol>
                        </div>

                        <div class="p-4 bg-slate-50 rounded-xl border border-slate-100">
                            <h4 class="font-bold text-slate-800 text-sm mb-2">Method 2: Command Line (elf-align check)</h4>
                            <p class="text-xs text-slate-600 mb-2 leading-relaxed">
                                Run standard shell tools on extracted shared objects (<code class="bg-slate-100 px-1 text-slate-700 font-mono">.so</code>) to check the segment alignments:
                            </p>
                            <div class="text-xs text-slate-200 font-mono bg-slate-900 p-3 rounded-lg overflow-x-auto">
objdump -p lib/arm64-v8a/*.so | grep LOAD
                            </div>
                            <p class="text-xs text-slate-400 mt-2">
                                If the alignment values displayed read <code class="bg-slate-800 text-slate-200 px-1 font-mono rounded">align 2**14</code> (which stands for 16,384 bytes, i.e., 16 KB), the library is perfectly aligned!
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
